		</table></td><td class="PanelBody" valign="Top"><table cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3" border="0" width="100%">
			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Vindicator<a name="60308"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Sep 3 04 5:37 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span><i>From a visiting monk, just passing by...</i>
<br />

<br />

<br />
Any FD class can split the guards, by taking advantage of the difference in the pathing routes taken by Vindi and his pets. Possibly other classes can use this same method, but the key is to first agro Vindi so that the pets are tied to him and pathing with him. I play a 65 monk and this works every time for me. 
<br />

<br />
1. Clear the arena, of course, and the left side guard there at the ice wall.
<br />

<br />
2. When Vindi gets close enough, agro him. (I toss a dart)
<br />

<br />
3. FD.
<br />

<br />
4. His pets will run out to meet up with him, nearest to you at the ice wall.
<br />

<br />
5. Then Vindi and his pets will begin walking back towards the Temple.
<br />

<br />
6. There is a &quot;magic&quot; spot when they get just past the halfway mark on the bridge.
<br />

<br />
7. The FD'd person gets up to regain agro, when they reach that magic spot.
<br />

<br />
8. Whereas Vindi has to run all the way back to the Temple before coming back to get you, the pets will come straight for you; i.e. Not running all the way back with Vindi. If you get up too soon, Vindi will come right for you, with the pets, instead of pathing to the Temple. (It may take a few tries to get it right, just keep trying.)
<br />

<br />
9. Tag them and hightail the two pets back to the Raidforce.
<br />

<br />
10. Vindi will be far out of assist range to come help his pets, by the time he turns around.
<br />

<br />
NOTE: To get far enough from his assist range, I find the best spot to set up for the pet split is at the top of the right ramp, by the Veteran you already killed.
<br />

<br />
11. Once pets are dead, set up your raidforce in the usual right corner in the arena where you can use the wall to balance Vindi.
<br />

<br />
12. Now go get Vindi solo. (I find that Vindi seems a little &quot;dazed&quot; minus his pets and loses agro for whatever reason, so you might have to babywalk him back to the raid.)
<br />

<br />
Voila!</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
